Write a C program to create a Doubly Linked List (DLL).
Each node contains an integer data field and two pointers:

next (points to the next node)
prev (points to the previous node).
The program should allow inserting n elements and display the DLL both forwards and backwards.


Constraints:
1 ≤ n ≤ 10^5
The values of each node: -10^6 ≤ data ≤ 10^6

Example:
Sample Input-1:

5  
10 20 30 40 50

Sample Output-1:

Forward: 10 20 30 40 50  
Backward: 50 40 30 20 10

Sample Input-2:

1  
100

Sample Output-2:

Forward: 100  
Backward: 100

 


Explanation:
createNode(int data) creates a new node with data.
appendNode() adds the node to the end of the DLL, updating both next and prev pointers.
displayForward() prints the list from head to tail.
displayBackward() prints the list from tail to head.
The program reads n from runtime input, then n integers, and builds the list accordingly.
Finally, it displays the list both forwards and backwards.

